# CATCH v2.1 — Release Notes

**Release date:** March 2026  
**Built by:** BIS · Tyler Technologies Courts & Justice  
**Supports:** TX OCA Community Pipeline · IL AOIC Community Pipeline

---

## What's new in v2.1

### Error Catalog (new tab)
Replaced the previous "Error Association" pivot with a purpose-built **Error Catalog** tab designed to support error library development. Every unique error ever seen across all stored history is deduplicated by `field + message + entity type` into a single flat table — one row per distinct error pattern.

Each row shows:
- Field name, entity type, and color-coded error category (Missing Field, Enum/Invalid Value, Type Error, Extra Field, Wrong Field Name, Invalid Entity Type)
- Full error message (hover to see untruncated)
- Occurrence count across all history
- Every publisher/CMS vendor who has sent that error, as chips
- Market (TX or IL)
- Translation/fix from the Error Library if one exists
- First seen and last seen timestamps

Live search filters across field, message, publisher, and entity type simultaneously. Market dropdown filters to TX or IL only. **Export CSV** produces a UTF-8 BOM-encoded spreadsheet with one row per unique error — occurrence count, semicolon-separated publisher list, envelope IDs, translation, and OCA reference code — ready to use as the foundation of an error library.

---

### Error Library search
The Error Library in Settings (⚙) now has a live search input above the entry list. Typing filters entries across field, translation, entity type, fix owner, match value, and recommended action. The count displays "Showing X of Y entries" when filtered. Save and Delete operations continue to work correctly against the underlying entry index regardless of what is filtered.

