---

### IL publisher fix
The Error Catalog was showing `(unknown)` for all IL errors because IL AOIC envelopes do not carry a `Publisher` field at the envelope level — the CMS vendor name is the `name` field on each individual entity.

This release fixes publisher propagation at every point in the data pipeline:

- **Run-level history:** `addToHistory` now falls back to `parsed.entities[0].name` when `parsed.publisher` is null (IL).
- **Per-error history:** Each error object stored in history now carries its own `publisher` field derived from the entity's `name`, so the catalog can correctly attribute errors even in mixed-vendor payloads.
- **Error Catalog:** `buildCatalogData` reads per-error publisher first, falling back to run-level publisher. IL errors now display the actual CMS vendor name (e.g. Journal Technologies, JANO Justice Systems) instead of `(unknown)`.

---

### Keyboard shortcut — Ctrl+Enter to validate
`Ctrl+Enter` (Windows / Linux) and `Cmd+Enter` (Mac) now trigger **Run Validation** from the input textarea. No need to reach for the button when iterating on a payload.

